  "text": "The dashboard JSON schema version migration pipeline in grafana/grafana is composed of coordinated Go backend and TypeScript frontend systems.\n\n## Backend Migration Pipeline (Go)\n\n### Core Migration Runner\nThe migration execution begins at `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/migrate.go`, which contains the `Migrate()` function that serves as the main entry point. The `Initialize()` function sets up the migrator singleton with dependencies. The migration process follows a strict sequence:\n\n1. Cleans up properties not included in frontend save models (`__elements`, `__inputs`, `__requires`)\n2. Tracks original transformations and fieldConfig.defaults.custom to preserve behavior\n3. Applies frontend DashboardModel and PanelModel constructor defaults via `applyFrontendDefaults()` (defined in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/frontend_defaults.go`)\n4. Applies panel defaults to all panels, including those in rows\n5. Ensures panel IDs are unique via `ensurePanelsHaveUniqueIds()` (in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migration_utils.go`)\n6. Executes version-specific migrations from v2 to the target version\n7. Adds built-in annotation queries\n8. Cleans up the dashboard for persistence\n\n### Migration Version Registry\nThe migration function registry is in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/migrations.go`. The `GetMigrations()` function returns a `map[int]SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` that maps schema version numbers (2-42) to their corresponding migration functions. This is the critical registry that orchestrates which migration function runs for each version. The `SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` type is defined as `func(context.Context, map[string]interface{}) error`.\n\n### Individual Migration Implementations\nEach schema version has a dedicated migration file in `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/schemaversion/`:\n- **v2.go** (V2): Migrates legacy services.filter structure\n- **v3-v8.go**: Various structural migrations including influxdb query schema updates\n- **v16.go** (V16): Grid layout upgrade from rows-based to grid-based\n- **v33.go** (V33): Replaces datasource names with references (uid and type)\n- **v36.go** (V36): Comprehensive datasource reference migration, handling annotations, template variables, and panels with proper UID-based object structures\n- **v37-v42.go**: Latest migrations including legend visibility normalization, table cell display migration, and hideFrom functionality updates\n\nMigrations v33 and v36 use the `DataSourceInfoProvider` interface to access datasource metadata dynamically, while most others use simple context-free functions.\n\n### Supporting Infrastructure\n- **frontend_defaults.go**: Applies frontend constructor defaults matching DashboardModel and PanelModel behavior\n- **migration_utils.go**: Helper functions like `ensurePanelsHaveUniqueIds()`, `GetBoolValue()`, `GetStringValue()`\n- **datasource_utils.go**: Utilities for datasource reference migration\n- **errors.go**: Custom migration error types\n- **conversion/**: Package for API version schema conversions (v0alpha1, v1beta1, v2alpha1, v2beta1)\n\n## Frontend Migration Pipeline (TypeScript)\n\n### Main DashboardMigrator Class\nThe `public/app/features/dashboard/state/DashboardMigrator.ts` implements the TypeScript counterpart that mirrors backend logic. The `DashboardMigrator` class accepts a `DashboardModel` in its constructor and provides the `updateSchema()` method. Key aspects:\n\n- **DASHBOARD_SCHEMA_VERSION constant**: Set to 42, the final schema version for v1 dashboard API (no new migrations should be added)\n- **updateSchema()** method: Iterates through schema versions with specific migration logic for each\n- Panel upgrade handlers system: Collects transformation functions in `panelUpgrades` array that are applied to all panels\n- Matches backend behavior for rows upgrade (v16), datasource migration (v33, v36), and all subsequent transformations\n\n### Supporting Frontend Components\n- **DashboardModel.ts**: The frontend dashboard data model that uses DashboardMigrator for schema upgrades\n- **PanelModel.ts**: Individual panel model handling\n- **getPanelPluginToMigrateTo.ts**: Handles automatic migration of legacy panel types (e.g., graph → timeseries/barchart)\n- **__tests__/migrationTestUtils.ts**: Testing utilities for migration validation\n\n## Integration Points\n\nThe backend migration is used when dashboards are persisted or loaded from storage, while the frontend migration is used when dashboards are loaded from the frontend JSON format. Version-specific logic includes:\n\n- **v8**: Influxdb query schema migration\n- **v16**: Rows to grid layout conversion with panel repositioning\n- **v20-v21**: Data link variable syntax updates\n- **v30**: Value mapping upgrades and tooltip option migrations\n- **v33**: Datasource name to reference conversion\n- **v34**: CloudWatch query multiple statistics splitting\n- **v36**: Comprehensive datasource UID-based reference migration\n- **v38**: Table cell display mode to cellOptions migration\n- **v39**: TimeSeriesTable transformer configuration updates\n- **v42**: HideFrom functionality with tooltip override\n\nThe pipeline ensures complete schema evolution from legacy formats to modern structured representations while maintaining backward compatibility and data integrity across Grafana versions."
}

